description:
Gray Area Festival 2019 
http://grayareafestival.io/
Gray Area Festival is San Francisco's premier annual festival advancing culture and common good through the lens of art and technology.

Salome Asega
http://www.salome.zone
Salome Asega is an artist and researcher based in New York City. She is currently a Technology Fellow in the Ford Foundations Creativity and Free Expression program and Director of Partnerships at POWRPLNT, a digital art collaboratory in Bushwick. Salome has participated in residencies and fellowships with Eyebeam, New Museum, The Laundromat Project, and Recess. She has exhibited and given presentations at the Shanghai Biennale, Performa, EYEO, and the Brooklyn Museum. Salome received her MFA from Parsons at The New School in Design and Technology where she also teaches.
